          "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/query.py\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"QuerySet.__iter__\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"QuerySet._fetch_all\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ModelIterable.__iter__\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"BaseIterable\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ValuesIterable.__iter__\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ValuesListIterable.__iter__\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"SQLCompiler.__init__\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"SQLCompiler.as_sql\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"SQLCompiler.execute_sql\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"SQLCompiler.results_iter\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Query.get_compiler\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Query\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"QuerySet.__iter__\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"QuerySet._fetch_all\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ModelIterable.__iter__\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/query.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Query.get_compiler\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"SQLCompiler.as_sql\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"django/django\",\n      \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"SQLCompiler.execute_sql\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"Django's QuerySet implements lazy evaluation through a two-phase approach: query building and query execution.\\n\\n**Lazy QuerySet SQL Compilation:**\\n\\nWhen a QuerySet is created and filtered (e.g., `Model.objects.filter(name='foo')`), the filtering methods in QuerySet return cloned instances with an updated Query object (django/db/models/sql/query.py). The Query object maintains all filter conditions, SELECT clauses, JOINs, and other SQL components in a lazy data structure. The actual SQL is not compiled until execution is explicitly triggered.\\n\\nThe SQL compilation happens in SQLCompiler.as_sql() (django/db/models/sql/compiler.py:763), which constructs the SQL string and parameters only when called. This method is invoked lazily, only when needed for execution.\\n\\n**QuerySet Iteration Trigger:**\\n\\nWhen a QuerySet is first iterated (e.g., via list(), for loop, or __iter__), the execution chain begins:\\n\\n1. QuerySet.__iter__() (django/db/models/query.py:396) is called\\n2. It calls QuerySet._fetch_all() (django/db/models/query.py:2093) to materialize results\\n3. _fetch_all() instantiates the appropriate Iterable class (typically ModelIterable) and converts it to a list\\n4. ModelIterable.__iter__() (django/db/models/query.py:91) is invoked\\n5. It calls query.get_compiler() (django/db/models/sql/query.py:364) to get a compiler instance\\n6. It calls compiler.execute_sql() (django/db/models/sql/compiler.py:1601)\\n\\n**Database Query Execution:**\\n\\nSQLCompiler.execute_sql() is where the actual database query is executed. This method:\\n1. Calls self.as_sql() to lazily compile the SQL (django/db/models/sql/compiler.py:1618)\\n2. Gets a database cursor via self.connection.cursor() (line 1629)\\n3. Executes the SQL via cursor.execute(sql, params) (line 1631) - THIS IS WHERE OperationalError OCCURS\\n\\nThe OperationalError is raised by the database driver (e.g., psycopg2, sqlite3, mysql) during cursor.execute() when there are database connectivity issues, invalid SQL, or other operational problems.\\n\\nOther Iterable classes (ValuesIterable, ValuesListIterable) follow the same pattern, calling compiler.results_iter() which in turn calls execute_sql() if results haven't been pre-fetched, ensuring all QuerySet variations use the same lazy compilation and execution mechanism.\"\n}\n",
